<tool_call>data_processing_validator
{
  "schema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "data": {"type": "object"}
    },
    "required": ["data"]
  },
  "data": {"data": {}},
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

I'll try an alternative approach by first converting the data to XML format before validation. I'll use the data_processing_transformer tool for this conversion.

<tool_call>data_processing_transformer
{
  "input_format": "json",
  "output_format": "xml",
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

            Since the transformer timed out, I'll try a different approach by using the data_processing_parser tool to parse the raw data we fetched from the API, which might handle the format conversion internally.

<tool_call>data_processing_parser
{
  "source": "https://api.example.com/data",
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

Now that we have successfully parsed the data, I'll attempt the validation step again using the data_processing_validator tool with the parsed output.

<tool_call>data_processing_validator
